  m_Name: IntroCombatDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  dialogue:
  - bodyText: Every round, the enemy gives you a couple opportunities to attack.
      Let's select an Action.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Each action has a Power range in which your Damage can fall.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: And a Speed which dictates the order in which you and your opponent's
      attacks will come out.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Target an enemy to declare the attack.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: This will queue up the action to attack, you can retrieve it back into
      your hand by tapping on its icon.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Each round, you can queue up as many attacks as you'd like. However...
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: 'You cannot play two actions that share the same speed. '
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: After all, if you could be in two places at once, they'd probably skip
      your exam entirely!
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Once you feel confident in your attacks, hit that confirm button to
      begin the bout
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Light work, lets kick things up a notch
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Light work, lets kick things up a notch
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: During the exam, you might find yourself outnumbered. Plan out your
      attack carefully
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: You might have noticed that while making some attacks, you get into
      this state of focus.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: However, it clears out at the end of the bout.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Make sure to capitalize and use that burst to take out your opponents.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Alright, time for the real warm up you've been waiting for.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: In a battle against a waste enemy, I've taught you to first read your
      opponent's intentions
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Use that to help plan your offensive
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: When you play a card against an enemy, your attacks will clash together.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Come at me!
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: 'During a clash, the attack that rolls the highest power wins, dealing
      all its power as damage to the loser. '
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Your mother always believed the best offense is the greatest defense.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Now, as the battle drags on, your deck of Actions will be slowly exhausted.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Alright, now it's for real, I'll use my fists to keep things fair.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Once exhausted, your deck will reshuffle. However, the maximum Actions
      you can hold will decrease by 1 everytime this happens.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Alright, now it's for real, I'll keep using my fists to keep things
      fair.
    speakerName: Ives
  - bodyText: Make sure to pace yourself!
    speakerName: Ives
